<TITLE> Fire destroys 250 shops in Bandarban </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bandarban, Mar 25 (bdnews24.com)  A fire destroyed around 250 shops at Bandarban's Alikadam Bazaar in the early hours of Thursday. There were no reports of casualties. A three-member committee, headed by the upazila's poll official Kaiser Mohammed and comprising the project implementation officer Md Ziaur Rahman and OC of Alikadam Police Station Niaz Mohammad, has been formed to investigate the fire. Administrative officials and locals said that the fire started at around 2.30am in Alikadam Bazaar, the business centre of the union. The fire consumed the whole market and initial estimates suggest the losses may amount to Tk three crores. Momtazuddin Ahmed, general secretary of Alikadam Press Club, told bdnews24.com that the fit started from a restaurant called Azmir Hotel and spread rapidly. The upazila nirbahee officer Nawab Aslam Habib added that "It is thought that the fire may have started from an oven at the hotel." The fire brigade and locals worked for four hours before the fire was bought under control. A delegation of local leaders headed by the constituency's MP Bir Bahadur visited the site after the fire. Bir Bahadur, who is also chief of the CHT development board sat with administrative officials in the morning. His press secretary, Sadek Hossain Chowdhury told journalists that the meeting discussed on ways to assist those affected by the fire. bd
